      <div xml:id="NA264-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu uṭaṉpōkāniṉṟa talaimakaṉ talaimakaḷai vaṟpuṟīiyatu.
            2. uṭaṉpōy maṟuttarāniṉṟār ūr kāṭṭi vaṟpuṟīiyatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. his is how HE who was eloping [with her] encouraged HER. 2. It is also how he was was bringing [her] back after eloping encouraged [HER] by poiting out the village.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA264">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            pāmpaḷaic ceṟiya muḻaṅki valaṉērpu</l>
<l>            vāṉṟaḷi poḻinta kāṇpiṉ kālai</l>
<l>            yaṇikiḷar kalāva maituvirit tiyalu</l>
<l>            maṇipurai yeruttiṉ maññai pōlaniṉ</l>
<l>            vīpey kūntal vīcuvaḷi yuḷara </l>
<l>            vēkuti maṭantai yelliṉṟu poḻutē</l>
<l>            vēypayi liṟumpiṟ kōvalar yātta</l>
<l>            vāpūṇ ṭeṇmaṇi yiyampu</l>
<l>            mutukāṇ ṭōṉṟumeñ ciṟunal lūrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>You may go, girl,</l>
<l rend="indent">so that the dashing wind whiffles your flower-wearing tresses,</l>
<l rend="indent2">like a peacock with a sapphire-like neck that moves forward,</l>
<l rend="indent2">spreading [its] decorative shining feathers wonderfully</l>
<l rend="indent">at the time of seeing when the drops were flowing<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">poḻinta</term>: here the <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> is awkward; we would expect either an infinitive or a verbal noun.</note> from the sky,</l>
<l rend="indent">forcefully risen [and] thundering for the snake to keep to [its] hole.</l>
<l rend="indent4">In the time when light fails</l>
<l>see yonder:</l>
<l rend="indent4">there appears our small good village,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the ornamental clear bells of the cows tied by the cowherds</l>
<l rend="indent4">make sound in the rustling bamboo thicket.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
